APOCALYPSE OF PAUL

YHWH (YHYYH) Codex

Paul awoke from the vision filled with the Holy Spirit and gave great thanks to YHWH. He returned to his companions and told them all the things he had seen and heard, strengthening their faith and urging them to live in holiness and repentance. And the Lord Jesus the Anointed commanded Paul saying “Go now and proclaim to all the world everything you have seen and heard, so that the children of men may repent while there is still time before the great and terrible day of judgment comes.” And the vision was closed and Paul returned fully to his body.
Then Paul saw the righteous shining like the sun in the kingdom of their Father YHWH, receiving crowns of glory and eternal inheritance, while the sinners remained in torment crying out for mercy that would not be granted in that hour. And the Lord commanded Paul to return to the earth and bear witness to all that he had seen, that men might repent and turn from their evil ways before the great day of judgment.
Then I Paul saw the heavens opened and the Son of Man sitting upon the throne of His glory with all His holy angels. And the books were opened and every soul was judged according to its deeds. The righteous entered into eternal life, but the wicked were cast into everlasting fire. Then the Lord showed Paul the paradise of the righteous where there is no night, only eternal light and joy, and the place of torment for the sinners where the worm does not die and the fire is not quenched.
Then Paul was caught up into the third heaven and heard unspeakable words which it is not permitted for a man to utter. And he saw the glory of YHWH and the order of the heavenly realms. And as Paul prayed, he was caught up into paradise and heard words that cannot be uttered. He saw the throne of YHWH surrounded by angels and the righteous in glory. Then he was sent back to proclaim the mystery of the kingdom.
And when He had said this, the Lord departed from Paul and he returned to his body. Then the Lord Jesus the Anointed appeared to Paul in great glory and transfigured him. And Paul said “Who are You, Lord?” And the Lord said “I am Yeshua whom you persecute. Stand upon your feet, for I have appeared to you to make you a minister and a witness.”
